<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="305" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1720,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="305">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,1829,1853]" pageId="3" pageNumber="305">Remarks.</emphasis>
The procursus, uncus and appendix of Huber’s (
<number box="[864,922,1828,1852]" pageId="3" pageNumber="305" value="2011.0">2011</number>
) 
<taxonomicName box="[938,1093,1828,1852]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracillimus">
<emphasis box="[938,1093,1828,1852]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="305">P. gracillimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
strikingly differ from those of the MSNG 
<typeStatus box="[282,384,1864,1888]" pageId="3" pageNumber="305">holotype</typeStatus>
. Thus, we consider Huber’s 
<taxonomicName box="[706,862,1864,1888]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracillimus">
<emphasis box="[706,862,1864,1888]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="305">P. gracillimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a misidentification. Future work may confirm that Huber’s 
<taxonomicName box="[250,408,1900,1924]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracillimus">
<emphasis box="[250,408,1900,1924]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="305">P. gracillimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a new species. In addition, the MSNG 
<typeStatus box="[896,994,1900,1924]" pageId="3" pageNumber="305">holotype</typeStatus>
is extremely similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Huber, 2011" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2011" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kohi">
<emphasis box="[1272,1350,1900,1924]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="305">P. kohi</emphasis>
Huber, 
<quantity box="[151,206,1936,1960]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.10794" pageId="3" pageNumber="305" unit="in" value="2011.0">2011</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in having two pairs of frontal apophyses on the male chelicerae, a dorsal apophysis on the pedipalpal femur, and similar shapes of procursus, uncus and appendix, and the locality of the MSNG 
<typeStatus box="[1093,1191,1972,1996]" pageId="3" pageNumber="305">holotype</typeStatus>
is within the range of the latter. We have not seen the 
<typeStatus box="[506,554,2009,2033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="305">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<emphasis box="[715,787,2008,2032]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="305">P. k o h i</emphasis>
, but we consider 
<taxonomicName box="[989,1065,2008,2032]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kohi">
<emphasis box="[989,1065,2008,2032]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="305">P. kohi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
dubious.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
